5.0 of 5 bubbles
The absolute best way to see Central Vietnam!
Jan 2020 • Couples
We’ve just come from spending a few days in Danang, HoiAn and Hue. During this time we relied on the local company Private Day Tour for both guiding and transport. Our primary guide was Vu but we also spent an amazing day with Tran. Our driver, Kien, was a gentle person and so good: we always felt safe with him at the wheel. From the moment we arrived at Danang Airport to when we boarded the plane to Ho Chi Minh some 8 days later, these individuals cared for us as though we were their parents. We are seniors and, unfortunately, my husband was ill much of the time we were there. Vu and Tran were always on time and very flexible if we had to modifying plans. They would contact us in the evening to ask how my husband was feeling and we so appreciated their concern. But most of all, they were wonderful tour guides. Both spoke excellent English and had great knowledge of the sites we visited and the history of Vietnam. Among our tours with them were Danang, HoiAn, Hue city tours, Marble Mountain, Monkey Mountain, Hai Van Pass as well as numerous museums and pagodas (too many to mention). We learned so much and saw so many things that we would not have seen on our own. We will cherish the time we spent wth them and highly recommend Private Day Tour (HoiAn, Danang & Hue).
Read more
Written January 15, 2020
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
Pawel B
Hua Hin, Thailand163 contributions
Unforgettable private sea fishing experience
Jun 2022
My wife and I love fishing. Upon our arrival we booked a private fishing tour with Vu through our hotel reception. Vu arranged it for us even though it was not fishing season and standard fishing tours were not available. Lucky us. Private fishing tour was a fantastic experience. From the early morning 5 am pick up at our hotel (Golden Holiday Hotel and Spa - see my other review) through barding the boat, sea fishing, BBQ lunch on board until return to the hotel around noon everything went very smoothly. We caught about 50 little pompanos, 20 puffer fish and few other unknown to us species. Some went back to the sea some we ate and will feed a local family. We hoped for a big one but catching the small ones was definitely more fun. Vu is a great guide and companion and we will definitely book more tours with him on our next trip. Highly recommended.
Written June 13, 2022
YShan
1 contribution
Informative trip to Marble Mountain and Lady Buddha with Mr Vu
Feb 2020
Had a memorable four-hour trip incl. transfer time with our guide, Mr Vu from Hoi An to Marble Mountain and Lady Buddha. Mr Vu is knowledgeable and has a good command of English. He is very familiar with the local attractions and led us directly to the main attraction sites without wasting any time. He is friendly and professional. My family and I have definitely learned more about Buddhism in Vietnam from Mr Vu. Thank you!!
